commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables the accessibility domain which causes `AXNodeId`s to remain consistent between method calls.
This turns on accessibility for the page, which can impact performance until accessibility is disabled.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables the CSS agent for the given page.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables the CSS agent for the given page. Clients should not assume that the CSS agent has been
enabled until the result of this command is received.

events.name: mediaQueryResultChanged
events.description:
Fires whenever a MediaQuery result changes (for example, after a browser window has been
resized.) The current implementation considers only viewport-dependent media features.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Stops observing for sinks and issues.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables DOM agent for the given page.

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables DOM agent for the given page.

events.name: documentUpdated
events.description: Fired when `Document` has been totally updated. Node ids are no longer valid.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables DOM snapshot agent for the given page.

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables DOM snapshot agent for the given page.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables storage tracking, prevents storage events from being sent to the client.

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables storage tracking, storage events will now be delivered to the client.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables database tracking, prevents database events from being sent to the client.

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables database tracking, database events will now be delivered to the client.

commands.name: clearGeolocationOverride
commands.description: Clears the overriden Geolocation Position and Error.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables headless events for the target.

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables headless events for the target.

events.name: targetCrashed
events.description: Fired when debugging target has crashed

events.name: targetReloadedAfterCrash
events.description: Fired when debugging target has reloaded after crash

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables log domain, prevents further log entries from being reported to the client.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables log domain, sends the entries collected so far to the client by means of the
`entryAdded` notification.

commands.name: forciblyPurgeJavaScriptMemory
commands.description: Simulate OomIntervention by purging V8 memory.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables network tracking, prevents network events from being sent to the client.

events.name: inspectModeCanceled
events.description: Fired when user cancels the inspect mode.

commands.name: resetNavigationHistory
commands.description: Resets navigation history for the current page.

commands.name: stopLoading
commands.description: Force the page stop all navigations and pending resource fetches.

events.name: interstitialHidden
events.description: Fired when interstitial page was hidden

events.name: interstitialShown
events.description: Fired when interstitial page was shown

commands.name: enable
commands.description: Enables the WebAudio domain and starts sending context lifetime events.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enable the WebAuthn domain and start intercepting credential storage and
retrieval with a virtual authenticator.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables console domain, prevents further console messages from being reported to the client.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables console domain, sends the messages collected so far to the client by means of the
`messageAdded` notification.

commands.name: pause
commands.description: Stops on the next JavaScript statement.

commands.name: stepOut
commands.description: Steps out of the function call.

events.name: resumed
events.description: Fired when the virtual machine resumed execution.

commands.name: stopPreciseCoverage
commands.description:
Disable precise code coverage. Disabling releases unnecessary execution count records and allows
executing optimized code.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables reporting of execution contexts creation.

commands.name: discardConsoleEntries
commands.description: Discards collected exceptions and console API calls.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables reporting of execution contexts creation by means of `executionContextCreated` event.
When the reporting gets enabled the event will be sent immediately for each existing execution
context.

commands.name: runIfWaitingForDebugger
commands.description: Tells inspected instance to run if it was waiting for debugger to attach.

events.name: executionContextsCleared
events.description: Issued when all executionContexts were cleared in browser
